The paper focuses on the optimization of radio resource management in multi-cell 5G networks, which is a topic closely related to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also addresses the challenge of user association, which involves system-level coordination and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses power control and scheduling, which are important aspects of multimedia communication (cs.MM) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
